{
  "name": "VMware Tanzu Platform",
  "namespace": "com.vmware.tanzu.platform",
  "contentPackId": "com.vmware.tanzu.platform",
  "framework": "#9c4",
  "version": "2.4",
  "author": "VMware by Broadcom",
  "url": "https://tanzu.vmware.com",
  "contentVersion": "1.1",
  "info": "<h3>VMware Tanzu Platform Content Pack</h3><p>Dashboards, extracted fields, and alerts for monitoring VMware Tanzu Platform (formerly Pivotal Cloud Foundry) deployments with VCF Operations for Logs.</p><h4>Components Covered:</h4><ul><li><b>Gorouter</b> - HTTP routing layer with request metrics</li><li><b>Diego</b> - Container orchestration (Rep, BBS, Auctioneer)</li><li><b>Cloud Controller</b> - API layer with CEF audit logging</li><li><b>UAA</b> - Authentication and authorization audit events</li><li><b>Garden</b> - Container runtime</li><li><b>Loggregator</b> - Log transport pipeline</li><li><b>Application Logs</b> - App stdout/stderr, staging, SSH</li></ul>",
  "instructions": "<h3>Setup Instructions</h3><ol><li>Configure your VMware Tanzu Platform deployment to forward syslog to this VCF Operations for Logs instance.</li><li>In Ops Manager: <b>TAS tile &gt; System Logging</b> - set syslog drain address (UDP 514 or TCP 1514 for TLS).</li><li>For component logs, configure <code>syslog-release</code> in your BOSH deployment.</li><li>For app logs, configure aggregate syslog drain or per-app syslog drain service.</li></ol><h4>Expected Syslog Sources:</h4><ul><li>Component logs via syslog-release (RFC 5424 with instance@47450)</li><li>Application logs via Loggregator (RFC 5424 with tags@47450)</li></ul>",
  "upgradeInstructions": "",
  "icon": "",
